{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d58a6649-60fb-4cbf-8005-8871cf5db3e6","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` syntax doesn't apply. MTP uses `--filter` with its own expression language. The equivalent is:\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey difference: **`&` → `and`** (also `|` → `or`, `!` → `not`). The `~` (contains) operator still works.\n\n### 2. Runner entry point\n\nYour `.csproj` already has `OutputType=Exe` and `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, so you're set there.\n\n### Alternative: run the executable directly\n\nWith MTP, the test project compiles to an executable. You can also run:\n\n```\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| VSTest filter | MTP filter |\n|---|---|\n| `A&B` | `A and B` |\n| `A\\|B` | `A or B` |\n| `!A` | `not A` |\n| `Prop~Value` | `Prop~Value` (same) |\n| `Prop=Value` | `Prop=Value` (same) |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"828241ad-1e81-460d-aef8-9a318cec66fb","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"A02C:2D289A:C7D9A8:E93C14:69FE87CE"},"id":"11882402-606a-4ed5-b617-5f7487620b64","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:03:18.377Z","parentId":"e7ecbe5b-8911-4249-afd3-065032a3b92a"}
